The paper proposes a novel nonlinear unit for deep neural networks and evaluates it on a number of datasets, indicating a focus on neural network architectures and machine learning. The use of the $L_p$ norm suggests a focus on optimization and regularization techniques, which are often studied in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The evaluation on benchmark datasets and the mention of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and object recognition suggest a focus on computer vision, which is often studied in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The mention of state-of-the-art results and the use of deep recurrent neural networks (RNN) suggest a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are often studied in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of HMAX models and neocognitrons suggests a focus on cognitive science and natural language processing, which are often studied in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
